OL,6,FIn an impact statement, the woman
OL,7,Fspoke about feeling nervous and unsafe
OL,8,Fin her house, and of being too
OL,9,Ffrightened to sleep there at night.
OL,11,FHeaney - whose dispute was with the
OL,12,Fwoman's daughter - admitted charges of
OL,13,Fattempted arson with intent to
OL,14,Fendanger life, threatening to damage
OL,15,For destroy property and sending an
OL,16,Foffensive or menacing message.
